Montserrat is a geometric sans-serif typeface
designed in 2011 by Julieta Ulanovsky, an
Argentine graphic designer. The font was
inspired by the posters, signs, and painted
windows from the first half of the 20th century
in the historic Montserrat neighborhood of
Buenos Aires. Some say that Montserrat is
similar to other fonts
